title: [BUG] Debug symbols for 3.119.0 are missing from nuget and ms symbol servers
body:
### Description

Symbols for 2.88.0 can be downloaded from both https://msdl.microsoft.com/download/symbols/ and https://symbols.nuget.org/download/symbols/. Symbols for 3.119.0 seem to be missing.

### Code

```
dotnet-symbol  ~/.nuget/packages/skiasharp.nativeassets.win32/3.119.0/runtimes/win-x64/native/libSkiaSharp.dll 
Downloading from https://msdl.microsoft.com/download/symbols/
ERROR: Not Found: C:\a\_work\1\s\externals\skia\out\windows\x64\libSkiaSharp.pdb - 'https://msdl.microsoft.com/download/symbols/libskiasharp.pdb/ac13267c46d9bc874c4c44205044422e1/libskiasharp.pdb'
```

```
dotnet-symbol --server-path https://symbols.nuget.org/download/symbols  ~/.nuget/packages/skiasharp.nativeassets.win32/3.119.0/runtimes/win-x64/native/libSkiaSharp.dll 
Downloading from https://symbols.nuget.org/download/symbols/
ERROR: 403 Forbidden: C:\a\_work\1\s\externals\skia\out\windows\x64\libSkiaSharp.pdb - 'https://symbols.nuget.org/download/symbols/libskiasharp.pdb/ac13267c46d9bc874c4c44205044422e1/libskiasharp.pdb'
```

### Expected Behavior

PDB gets downloaded

### Actual Behavior

It is not

### Version of SkiaSharp

3.116.0 (Current)
